Just wanted to share how I solved this, using a mixin class, that uses TestCase  setUp and tearDown to mimic the __enter__ and __exit__ behavior of responses, and adds an (optional) default response.

```python
import responses


class ResponsesMixin(object):
    def setUp(self):
        responses._default_mock.__enter__()
        self.add_default_response()
        super(ResponsesMixin, self).setUp()

    def tearDown(self):
        super(ResponsesMixin, self).tearDown()
        responses._default_mock.__exit__()

    def add_default_response(self):
        """ Override to add default response/s for all test runs """
        pass
```

