@bjwatson Its ok for this to be done post beta.
@lukesneeringer I was going to point to `database.read` or `database.execute_sql` as an example where this could happen if one did not completely consume the iterator returned by them. I thought they would hang on to the session till the stream is closed. But I realized those methods are buggy. I filed an issue for them:
