@alexanderrichards `sleep_until_completed()` will basically call `runMonitoring()` on a job which in turn sets the monitoring system's list of jobs to be just that job. It will then sleep until the various monitoring threads have finished monitoring those jobs.

`run_until_completed()` will run the monitoring code serially in the main thread without all the overhead of the multi-threaded monitoring system.

Even with the wait time between monitoring system runs set to zero seconds, it still takes longer than with `run_until_completed()`.

